433
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:19,530
Scott: Yeah, regular DS games, GBA games, GameCube games can run on that, right?

434
00:24:19,951 --> 00:24:29,090
Scott: You know, you put all those games in there, not free, but the NES, SNES, Game Boy, Game Boy Color games, all just all free, period, all of them.

435
00:24:29,210 --> 00:24:31,126
Scott: You get everything, right, in those 32 gigs.

436
00:24:31,652 --> 00:24:32,690
Scott: It's already installed.

437
00:24:32,953 --> 00:24:34,450
Scott: As soon as you buy the thing, you need to do everything.

438
00:24:34,732 --> 00:24:36,970
Rym: I would have been a little more subtle to make a little more money.

439
00:24:37,070 --> 00:24:40,230
Rym: What I would have done is made NES games free.

440
00:24:40,370 --> 00:24:42,110
Rym: The entire catalog for everyone forever free.

441
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:44,770
Scott: Or, you know, if you want to make a little bit of money, here's what you can do, right?

442
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:50,283
Scott: You can say, "Yeah, okay, 10 bucks gets you every NES game, 10 bucks gets you every

443
00:24:50,303 --> 00:24:50,385
Scott: SNES.".

444
00:24:50,730 --> 00:24:55,910
Scott: You know, huge bundles for low prices on the oldest games in big, you know, like that.

445
00:24:56,651 --> 00:25:02,230
Rym: Yeah, or, you know, do NES games free just because you gotta have something free so people just buy this thing outright.

446
00:25:02,714 --> 00:25:08,110
Scott: You can put the greatest NES hits on there for free, all the ones people really want to play, and then all the rest in a bundle for 10 bucks.

447
00:25:08,570 --> 00:25:19,550
Rym: Or what I would do is make a subscription model where, you know, NES games free, whatever, but everything else-- Oh, Spotify, $5 a month, and as soon as you stop paying, all the games go away?

448
00:25:19,891 --> 00:25:24,170
Rym: Yep, 5 or 10 bucks a month, you know, a relatively small amount, but not just on that device.

449
00:25:24,711 --> 00:25:27,985
Scott: If you pay for that, you log into a computer, it works on your computer.

450
00:25:29,271 --> 00:25:31,810
Rym: Every device that they make or that is open.

451
00:25:32,112 --> 00:25:34,330
Scott: Wii, PC, DS, everything.

452
00:25:34,690 --> 00:25:39,470
Rym: Hell, with them, I would try to make a deal with Microsoft and get it all in the XBLA, but you gotta pay 10 bucks a month for it.

453
00:25:39,630 --> 00:25:44,250
Scott: I would make a controller that can work with Netflix and try to get the games into Netflix.

454
00:25:44,691 --> 00:25:46,450
Rym: Oh, that would be eminently doable.

455
00:25:46,510 --> 00:25:48,110
Rym: The Roku could probably do it.

