00:25:48,272 --> 00:25:48,750
Scott: No shit.

457
00:25:49,051 --> 00:25:51,329
Rym: The thing is, Nintendo is married-- So they're old games.

458
00:25:51,450 --> 00:25:54,430
Rym: But Scott, Nintendo is married to the hardware market.

459
00:25:54,550 --> 00:25:57,670
Scott: They're going to be-- They're also married to the idea that games should cost a lot of money.

460
00:25:57,770 --> 00:26:01,810
Rym: I believe Nintendo is going to be the last proprietary console in the world.

461
00:26:02,418 --> 00:26:02,670
Scott: Maybe.

462
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:07,910
Rym: I think Sony consoles, PS3, I think they're going to slowly disappear or edge toward commodity.

463
00:26:08,410 --> 00:26:12,308
Rym: I think Microsoft eventually just-- If you buy an Xbox, it's just a PC.

